-- Power Grid, ICICI Bank, SpiceJet, Reliance Power: India Equity Preview
-- B y   R u t h   D a v i d   a n d   R a j h k u m a r   K   S h a a w
-- 2010-11-08T02:51:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-08/power-grid-corp-of-india-spicejet-reliance-power-india-equity-preview.html
The following companies may have
 unusual  price changes in India  trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of the  last close .  The Bombay Stock Exchange Sensitive Index, or  Sensex , rose
111.39, or 0.5 percent, to 21,004.96. The S&P CNX  Nifty  Index on
the National Stock Exchange advanced 0.5 percent to 6,312.45.
The  BSE 200 Index  increased 0.5 percent to 2,660.38.  SGX S&P CNX
Nifty Index futures  for November delivery declined 0.2 percent
to 6,334 at 10:36 a.m. in Singapore.  ICICI Bank Ltd.  (ICICIBC IN): The country’s second-biggest
lender plans to sell 10-year bonds denominated in U.S. dollars
as soon as today, according to a person familiar with the
matter. Barclays Plc, Citigroup Inc. and Deutsche Bank AG are
managing the benchmark sale, said the person, who asked not to
be identified because the details are private. Benchmark
typically means at least $500 million. The shares gained 0.6
percent to 1,273.35 rupees.  Power Grid Corp. of India Ltd.  (PWGR IN): The state-run
company plans to spend 226.5 billion rupees ($5.1 billion) to
implement 12 projects, the Press Trust of India reported
yesterday, citing a statement from Chairman  S.K. Chaturvedi .  Separately, the nation’s biggest transmission company will
sell shares for between 80 rupees and 90 rupees apiece starting
tomorrow, the state-owned company said in an advertisement in
the Economic Times newspaper. Power Grid employees and retail
investors will be eligible for 5 percent discount to the offer
price, it said. The shares rose 0.5 percent to 102.05 rupees.  Reliance Power Ltd.  (RPWR IN): Billionaire  Anil Ambani ’s
company announced a $5 billion line of credit from the Export-
Import Bank of the U.S. yesterday, to be used for renewable
energy and gas plants. The shares fell 0.2 percent to 164.9
rupees.  SpiceJet Ltd.  (SJET IN): The discount airline will buy 30
commercial aircraft from Boeing Co. in a deal worth about $2.7
billion, the White House press secretary said in a statement on
Nov. 6. The shares rose 1.9 percent to 89.15 rupees.  State Bank of India  (SBIN IN ): The biggest lender plans to
acquire a second bank in Indonesia for about $100 million, the
Financial Express reported, citing Deputy Managing Director
 Pratip Chaudhuri . The bank plans to set up a unit in Australia
and open branches in the Netherlands and Italy, it said. The
shares climbed 1.7 percent to 3,489.95 rupees.  To contact the reporter on this story:
